  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Humanitarian Assistance to the People Affected by Typhoon Tisoy</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through this project, IOM, in partnership with Plan International, is providing urgent shelter, water, sanitation and hygiene (WASH), food, and livelihood support to 1,300 families (6,500 individuals) in the most affected municipalities by the Typhoon Tisoy in Camarines Sur and Sorsogon (Philippines). To ensure the most appropriate intervention is provided to the wider affected populations across the region, this intervention will use mixed modalities (in-kind, voucher &amp; cash) in delivering assistance on shelter, WASH, food, and livelihood. Community-based trainings will be provided to coincide with distribution of shelter kits and grants to ensure proper and sustainable use of the shelter assistance.</narrative>
  </description>
